        "title": "feat(ios): modernize the app with iOS 26 Liquid Glass",
        "body": "Related: #98317\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe iOS app mixed custom card glass, gradients, compact controls, and inconsistent corner geometry across its primary tabs. That weakened hierarchy on iOS 26, made content compete with system chrome, and left several navigation-adjacent controls looking older than the platform around them.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis modernizes the shared iOS design system around Apple's iOS 26 guidance: native Liquid Glass for interactive chrome, quiet semantic surfaces for content, shared concentric geometry, a minimizing tab bar, and one shared notice pattern. The deployment target remains iOS 18; every iOS 26 API is availability-gated with a functional bordered/material fallback.\n\nThe design audit is captured in `apps/ios/DESIGN.md`, informed by Apple's [Adopting Liquid Glass](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/technologyoverviews/adopting-liquid-glass), [Applying Liquid Glass to custom views](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/applying-liquid-glass-to-custom-views), and [Build a SwiftUI app with the new design](https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/323/) guidance.\n\n## User Impact\n\nControl, Talk, Agent, Settings, transient notices, and shared content cards now present a more coherent native hierarchy. Primary actions and header controls adopt iOS 26 Liquid Glass, content cards remain calm and readable, the tab bar minimizes while scrolling, Agent no longer shows a duplicate navigation title, and earlier iOS versions retain equivalent actions and accessibility semantics.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- iPhone 17 simulator, iOS 26.5, Xcode 26.6.\n- `RootTabsSourceGuardTests` + `SwiftUIRenderSmokeTests`: 43/43 passed after the final review fix.\n- `OpenClawSnapshotUITests.testConnectedGatewayTabs`: passed with five deterministic primary-tab captures.\n- `OpenClawSnapshotUITests.testLiveGatewayControlOverviewNavigation`: passed end to end against a real isolated OpenClaw Gateway; connected through setup, opened Control, navigated into Overview, and asserted `Back to Control` without a crash.\n- Production SwiftFormat lint and `git diff --check`: passed.\n- Structured Codex autoreview: one accepted semantic-color finding fixed; final pass clean with no actionable findings (0.93 confidence).\n\n### Before and after\n\nMatched iPhone 17 / iOS 26.5 captures follow below. Both sides use the same deterministic connected fixture and light appearance.\n\n| Screen | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Control | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Control before: dense custom surfaces and small corner geometry\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7bd51438-942a-42c8-bfef-ccd5773776fa\" /> | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Control after: quiet grouped cards and modern concentric geometry\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/84aa2862-8720-46cc-b930-46d84ea7085b\" /> |\n| Chat | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Chat before\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d13d646e-200b-46c8-8ac9-59426c7a5bfb\" /> | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Chat after: system chrome aligned with the shared visual language\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/00a8e0ca-831f-4a4f-ac7c-77c083ab47ef\" /> |\n| Talk | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Talk before: opaque custom primary action\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d27809dd-cd8e-41e2-8d46-4fcf4fb76a57\" /> | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Talk after: native prominent Liquid Glass primary action\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dae7c2ae-4a74-4327-86b1-a6d0f67e30cd\" /> |\n| Agent | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Agent before: custom header and filter chrome\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6eae27e5-8d5e-497b-a0d6-da14c2639399\" /> | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Agent after: one adaptive title and grouped native glass controls\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c5fcb05a-e5de-42be-8244-c4f05897d3dc\" /> |\n| Settings | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Settings before: tight card geometry\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a555831e-e4e5-4a07-9938-e3caacac6e3a\" /> | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Settings after: consistent shared content-card geometry\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/977a149b-7c71-43cd-8abd-1f170f3308fd\" /> |\n\n### Live Gateway proof\n\nThese captures come from the real Gateway test rather than the deterministic fixture: first the connected Control screen, then the opened Overview destination.\n\n| Connected Control | Overview opened |\n|---|---|\n| <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Live OpenClaw Gateway connected on the Control screen\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/00e8ef92-2699-4b06-9f52-686c0d4a767b\" /> | <img width=\"320\" alt=\"Live Gateway Overview destination opened without a crash\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/408c5533-ca05-42dc-b87f-284d89f70e82\" /> |\n",
